All three cases work as expected.

Created `src/cli.ts`. It:

- **Reads JSON from stdin** — accumulates the full input stream (`readStdin`) and parses it as a request object.
- **Dispatches on an `operation` field** to the existing `claim-office.js` module:
  - `"quote"` → `quote(customer, items, options)`
  - `"claim"` → `claim(items, incident)`
- **Writes JSON to stdout** — serializes the result with a trailing newline.
- **Handles errors** — unknown operations and module-thrown errors (e.g. unknown item types) go to stderr with exit code 1.

Verified live via stdin:
- Single sword (newcomer) → `{"premium":115}` ✓ (matches the spec example)
- Sword claim, 300 damage → `{"payout":200,"remainingCap":1800}` ✓
- Unknown operation → error on stderr, `exit=1` ✓

One note: this was a plain file-creation/wiring task, not a TDD cycle, so I created it directly rather than going through the red/green/refactor skills — there was no new behavior in `claim-office.ts` to test-drive, only an I/O entry point around the existing module.
